const faqs = [
  { q: "Which Miele wall oven models do you see in LA kitchens?", a: "The H 7000 MasterChef 30\" built-in is Miele's current flagship wall oven generation and the model we service most often in LA's integrated-kitchen remodel work. H 7000 ships with Miele's MasterChef auto-program library (hundreds of pre-programmed cook profiles) and integrates into flush-mount cabinetry with Miele's precision alignment tolerance. DGC Combi-Steam 24\" and 30\" variants (combi-steam is pure steam + convection in one cavity) show up at higher-end Westside and Hollywood Hills kitchens where serious cooks specified the steam capability during renovation. Pure Convection H 2000-series is the mainstream tier below H 7000. Speed Oven (microwave + convection combo) rounds out the Miele wall-oven column for kitchens wanting an integrated reheat+bake capability at a smaller 24\"/30\" footprint. Legacy H 6000 and earlier generations still run at long-established LA Miele installs." },
  { q: "Is Miele the same company as Bosch or Thermador?", a: "No. This is a common LA Miele kitchen customer question and the answer matters for parts supply and service expectations. <b>Miele</b> is Miele & Cie. KG, a family-owned German company based in Gütersloh, privately held by the Miele and Zinkann families since the 1899 founding. <b>Bosch + Thermador + Gaggenau + Siemens</b> are all BSH Hausgeräte brands (Bosch subsidiary). The two companies share no engineering, no parts, and no service network. Miele's parts-supply for US service routes through Miele USA's Princeton NJ headquarters and authorized service partners; BSH routes through Irvine CA. LA customers who have a Miele wall oven + Bosch dishwasher + Thermador range are running three distinct parts chains." },
  { q: "My Miele DGC Combi-Steam oven shows a descaling reminder — what does service involve?", a: "DGC Combi-Steam uses a water boiler inside the cavity to produce steam for combi-steam cooking, and LA's hard water chemistry deposits mineral scale on the boiler heating element + internal plumbing over cycle hours. Miele's control logic tracks boiler run-time and prompts descaling at specific thresholds — typically after 500-1,000 steam cycles depending on cavity variant. Descaling service: we run Miele-authorized descaling solution through the boiler circuit, verify the boiler drain clears, confirm the steam-generation sensor reads within spec, and check the electromechanical water valve for scale-related cycling issues. For LA hard-water areas (Valley, parts of the Westside), annual descaling is often the right service cadence — operators who skip descaling past the reminder threshold can burn out the boiler element, which runs $480-$780 to replace versus $260-$420 for the descaling service itself." },
  { q: "Miele MasterChef auto-programs stopped working — control board or firmware?", a: "MasterChef is Miele's auto-program library running inside the control board firmware — it's not a separate sub-component, it's a feature of the main electronics. When MasterChef programs fail to execute correctly (wrong cycle parameters, programs missing from the menu, cycle abort mid-program), the diagnostic sequence is: check firmware revision against current Miele-published version, attempt factory reset + profile reload (user-specific settings wipe but MasterChef library restores), verify sensor feedback during a test cycle (MasterChef relies on temperature + humidity sensor inputs), and read control-board error log if the display shows a specific fault code. Firmware update resolves roughly 30% of MasterChef faults; factory reset resolves another 25%; control-board replacement needed in the remaining cases, running $620-$980 on current-generation H 7000 (board is higher-cost than mainstream brands because Miele-specialty electronics)." },
  { q: "Do you service Miele wall ovens at the flush-mount installation spec LA modernist kitchens require?", a: "Yes — flush-mount installation discipline is specifically where Miele wall oven service differentiates from generalist oven service. Miele's integrated-kitchen aesthetic depends on the appliance sitting precisely flush with surrounding cabinetry, with consistent gap lines on all four sides of the appliance face. During any service call requiring the unit to be partially pulled (element replacement, control board work, major diagnostic access), our reinstall maintains the original flush-mount alignment within millimeter tolerance. LA's Eichler + Case Study + contemporary architectural kitchens with Miele wall ovens depend on this — a wall oven that's reinstalled 3mm proud of the cabinet face after service is immediately visible and devalues the kitchen's design intent. Our Miele reinstall approach includes shim adjustment at the mounting brackets, final gap verification at all four edges, and handoff walk-through with the customer to confirm flush-mount integrity." },
  { q: "What does Miele wall oven repair cost in LA?", a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Miele wall oven service runs at luxury-tier pricing reflecting Miele-specialty parts channel: DGC Combi-Steam boiler descaling $260-$420; water valve replacement $280-$460; steam-generation sensor $320-$520; MasterChef firmware update + profile reload $180-$320; bake element (H 7000 or H 2000) $420-$680; convection fan motor $480-$780; control board (H 7000 current generation) $620-$980; door hinge $280-$480; door glass $420-$720; thermostat $340-$540; DGC boiler element replacement $480-$780; oven cavity door-lock motor (self-clean models) $320-$520. Miele parts run 5-14 days lead time on specialty components through Miele USA Princeton NJ distribution; common service parts stocked more widely." }
];

