    <p>Miele & Cie. KG was founded in 1899 in Gütersloh, Germany, and remains privately held by the Miele and Zinkann families. That corporate structure matters for Miele wall oven service in LA because Miele's engineering and parts-supply priorities are set by the founding families rather than by conglomerate integration pressures — the product line preserves Miele-specific engineering conventions that an ITW or BSH-owned brand wouldn't carry. LA's modernist and integrated-kitchen remodel work specifies Miele heavily because of this consistency; customers who chose Miele five years ago get the same flush-mount integration discipline from the 2026 lineup.</p>
    <p>Miele USA runs distribution from Princeton NJ. Parts-supply lead times for LA service: common components (bake elements, sensors, door hardware) stocked at distributor level with 1-3 day lead; specialty components (Combi-Steam boiler elements, current-generation control boards, specific Miele-specialty electronics) run 5-14 days through Princeton. We stock common Miele service parts on the truck for single-visit resolution; specialty parts require a return visit once parts land.</p>
