  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>DGC Combi-Steam descaling — LA hard water service cadence</h2>
    <p>DGC Combi-Steam ovens depend on an internal water boiler to generate steam for combi-steam cooking cycles. LA water chemistry runs hard in much of the Valley, parts of Pasadena, and specific Westside pockets — which deposits mineral scale on the boiler heating element and internal plumbing over cycle hours. Miele's control logic tracks boiler run-time and prompts descaling at thresholds — typically 500-1,000 steam cycles depending on model. When the descaling reminder appears, the service call covers running Miele-authorized descaling solution through the boiler circuit, verifying boiler drain clears, checking steam-generation sensor spec, and inspecting the electromechanical water valve for scale-related cycling issues.</p>
    <p><b>Service cadence for LA hard-water areas</b>: annual descaling is often the right rhythm for households running DGC Combi-Steam regularly. Operators who skip descaling past the reminder threshold risk burning out the boiler element itself — element replacement runs $480-$780 versus $260-$420 for descaling service. The math strongly favors staying on schedule.</p>
    <p><b>What descaling doesn't fix</b>: if the boiler element has already burnt out, descaling doesn't restore it — boiler element replacement is the repair at that point. If the water valve has scale-seized, valve replacement ($280-$460) resolves. We verify at diagnostic whether the cycle fault is descale-responsive or hardware-repair territory before quoting.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Flush-mount installation discipline — LA modernist kitchens</h2>
    <p>Miele's integrated-kitchen aesthetic depends on flush-mount precision. The appliance face sits flush with surrounding cabinetry, with consistent gap lines on all four sides — top, bottom, left, right. LA's Eichler homes, Case Study mid-century modernist kitchens, and contemporary architectural renovations depend on this discipline being maintained through the appliance's service life.</p>
    <p>Our Miele wall oven service approach preserves flush-mount integrity through every service call:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Partial-pull method</b> — when a service call requires accessing the unit's interior wiring or rear panel, we pull the unit only as far as access requires, not as a default full-pull.</li>
      <li><b>Cabinet-preservation pads</b> — protective pads on surrounding cabinet panels during any partial-pull service to prevent scratching or marring of custom-panel cabinetry.</li>
      <li><b>Shim adjustment at reinstall</b> — the mounting brackets carry shim adjustments that allow fine-tuning flush-mount alignment after reinstall; we verify adjustment before securing.</li>
      <li><b>Gap-line verification at all four edges</b> — we measure and confirm consistent gaps at top/bottom/left/right before finishing the call.</li>
      <li><b>Customer walk-through</b> — we show the customer the final flush-mount state before leaving, so any alignment concern gets addressed on-site rather than surfacing after.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This discipline is why Miele customers who've had prior service experiences with generalist appliance repair techs often book with us specifically for Miele work — the reinstall alignment matters more on Miele than on most other brands.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Miele wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>MasterChef firmware glitches</b> — auto-programs fail to execute correctly, programs missing from menu, cycle abort mid-program. Firmware update or factory reset resolves most; control board replacement in remaining cases.</p>
    <p><b>Combi-Steam descale overdue</b> — LA hard water scale on boiler element + plumbing. Descaling service $260-$420; deferred descale can escalate to boiler element replacement.</p>
    <p><b>Water valve scale-seized</b> — combi-steam water intake valve fails from scale accumulation. Replacement $280-$460.</p>
    <p><b>Steam-generation sensor drift</b> — combi-steam cycle aborts because sensor reads out of spec. Replacement $320-$520.</p>
    <p><b>Bake element failure</b> — H 7000 + H 2000 bake elements fail over years of thermal cycling. Replacement $420-$680.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor bearings</b> — noise and wobble develop with bearing wear. Replacement $480-$780.</p>
    <p><b>Control board (H 7000)</b> — when firmware update and reset don't resolve. Replacement $620-$980 (higher than mainstream brands reflecting Miele specialty electronics pricing).</p>
    <p><b>Door hinge wear</b> — precision-cut Miele door hinges develop play over years. Replacement $280-$480.</p>
